  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-9">
        <h3><i><font face="verdana" color="darkblue">"What is The Brewer's Edge?"</font><i></h3>
        <p>The concept is simple: Let's create an social network where home beer brewers can have their beers rated by fans, and other brewers alike, without the effort of a formal brewing competition. Craft beer enthusiasts can share reviews, ideas, recipes and revel in all that is the bubbly libation!  All the while, brewers can use the info to become better at their craft.</p>

        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-3 col-lg-3" align="bottom">
            <%= image_tag "obb-logo150x90.png", :height => '90%', :width => '90%' %>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-9">
            <h3><i><font face="verdana" color="darkblue">"Sweet! But how do I sign up?"</font></i></h3>
            <p>Check out the form to the right (or below for mobile users). Sign up is incredibly simple. All users sign up with a valid email, username and password. </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3><i><font face="verdana" color="darkblue">"Okay, I'm in. Now what?"</font></i></h3>
        <p>Here's the fun part! Home Brewers, are you ready to raise your game? Load all of your recipes through your profile page. After you've created a real batch of beer, create a virtual batch on the site.  It's easy, just tell us how the batch came out.  Once you hand out your beer your fans will be able to come back to the site and rate the experience.  When you've collected the feedback from those reviews, use it to improve your process and become a better brewer.</p>
      </div>


    <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-3">
    <h2>Log in</h2>
    <%= simple_form_for(resource, as: resource_name, url: session_path(resource_name)) do |f| %>
        <div class="form-inputs">
          <%= f.input :email, required: false, autofocus: true %>
          <%= f.input :password, required: false %>
          <%= f.input :remember_me, as: :boolean if devise_mapping.rememberable? %>
        </div>
        <div class="form-actions">
          <%= f.button :submit, "Log in" %>
        </div>
        <% end %>

      <%= render "devise/shared/links" %>
    </div>
  </div>
